<br>
A guild that consists ONLY of wizards..... is going to do very poorly later in the game, especially since you do not have the class balance required in capable solid groups. Guilds that consist of mixed classes work out better. <br>
<br>
HOWEVER -- <br>
<br>
There is nothing to discourage players from forming informal associations of any class or race of characters. Think of them as informal gathering of friends whose characters share a close interest, the same race, the same profession, etc.  It does not have to be a guild at all.  <br>
<br>
for example, <br>
<br>
Dwarven Oktoberfest Union (boozing dwarves only)<br>
<br>
Council of the Burning Wizards (wizards only)<br>
<br>
Children of the Plague (Bertoxxulous worshippers only)<br>
<br>
These are three names that I heard thrown about for strictly nonguild associations on this server.  I think they are awesome ideas.  The third one.... is one that I would be in if it ever formed, and had discussed with 2 friends already.  They are simply informal support groups of like minded characters.... especially so that we can develop our characters for role playing purposes, share ideas, etc. They are not replacements for guilds, however.  <br>
